(37, 'Nguyen Anh Ngoc, MBA', 'https://vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Nguyen-Anh-Ngoc-e1605179709966-768x567.jpg', 'Head of Student Affairs Management', '<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">Ms. Nguyen Anh Ngoc earned a Bachelor’s degree in Finance &amp; Securities at the Banking Academy of Vietnam. Her thirst&nbsp; for knowledge and advanced education brought her to the University of La Verne, California, where she completed an MBA degree in Finance &amp; Accounting.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">As a progressive individual who is open to change, Ngoc never hesitates to take on new roles. Over the past 7 years in Vinschool, she has been in charge of several positions including Assistant to CEO, Head of Operation Department, Head of Admissions &amp; Customer Care in Southern region, Vice Principal of Vinschool Central Park Secondary &amp; High school, Vice Principal of Vinschool Golden River Primary – Secondary &amp; High school, and most recently Director of HR &amp; Training.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">As her new role as the “Captain” of Student Affairs team, she will be responsible for the development of positive outcomes regarding student satisfaction. She will focus on partnering with other areas within the University and coordinate specific programs that will support student learning and assist students with both academic and personal issues.</p>', '2021-08-29', b'0', b'1', 1),
(38, 'Hanh Bui, MA', 'https://vinuni.edu.vn/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Hanh-Bui-scaled-e1593013267594-768x567.jpg', 'Head of External Engagement\r\nFellow, Faculty of Arts & Sciences\r\n\r\nArts and Sciences', '<h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(46, 82, 136); font-size: 1.375rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">BIOGRAPHY</h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem; padding-inline-start: 2rem; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Hanh Bui is the Director of External Engagement of VinUniversity cum Director of “<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">The Vingroup Science and Technology Scholarship Program for Master’s and Doctoral Degrees for Overseas Stud</em>y”.</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Prior to joining VinUniversity, Hanh has had more than 10 years of work experience with the UK and US governments. She served as Vice-Consul at the British Embassy, Hanoi for almost 2 years. Prior to that, she worked for the Vietnam Education Foundation (VEF), an independent U.S. Federal Government agency, for eight years, as&nbsp;Senior Program Manager. At VEF, Hanh managed three educational exchange programs which sent more than 650 Vietnamese nationals to the U.S. for Master’s/Ph.D. studies and post-doctoral training and almost 60 U.S. professors to teach courses in Vietnam.</li></ul><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(46, 82, 136); font-size: 1.375rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">PROFESSIONAL INTERESTS</h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem; padding-inline-start: 2rem; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Education exchange</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Cross-cultural communication</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Women’s empowerment</li></ul><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(46, 82, 136); font-size: 1.375rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">TEACHING INTERESTS</h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem; padding-inline-start: 2rem; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">English as a Second Language</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Community Service</li></ul><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(46, 82, 136); font-size: 1.375rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">SELECTED AWARDS AND HONORS</h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem; padding-inline-start: 2rem; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Vietnamese Goodwill Ambassador for the City of Palmerston North, New Zealand, May 2017</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Certificate of High Academic Achievements, Massey University, August 2016</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Full Master’s scholarship award by the New Zealand Agency for International Development (NZAid) for Vietnamese scholars, January 2016</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Certificates of Excellence from the VEF Executive Director in summers 2009, 2010, 2011, and 2012 for the exceptional contributions to the VEF mission</li></ul><h3 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(46, 82, 136); font-size: 1.375rem; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\">EDUCATION</h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem; padding-inline-start: 2rem; color: rgb(62, 62, 62); font-family: Montserrat, sans-serif;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Master’s Degree: Massey University, New Zealand, 2017</li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit;\">Bachelor’s Degree: Vietnam National University, Hanoi, 2005</li></ul>', '2021-08-29', b'0', b'1', 1),
